&lt;p&gt;Location: Remote (East Coast hours preferred)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Code3 is an integrated marketing agency built for the modern consumer journey. We sit at the intersection of Connected Media, Creative, and Commerce, helping some of the world&#39;s most recognized brands and fastest-growing challengers turn attention into business growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paid social has evolved far beyond media buying. Success today requires understanding consumer behavior, creative performance, platform innovation, and how culture influences the way people discover and buy products. Our team partners with clients to build full funnel strategies that connect all of those pieces—combining data, creativity, testing, and measurement to drive meaningful business results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe the best ideas come from people who are endlessly curious, willing to challenge conventional thinking, and excited to experiment. We work collaboratively across media, creative, measurement, strategy, and platform partnerships to continuously push our clients and ourselves forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Paid Social Strategist, you&#39;ll serve as the strategic lead across a portfolio of clients, helping shape how some of today&#39;s most recognizable consumer brands grow through paid social platforms including Meta, TikTok, Pinterest, and YouTube.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll develop full funnel media strategies, uncover new testing opportunities, guide creative direction through performance insights, and translate complex data into clear business recommendations. You&#39;ll partner closely with client strategy, measurement, creative, and platform teams to deliver integrated solutions that move beyond campaign performance and drive measurable business growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success in this role requires equal parts analytical thinking, creative curiosity, and commercial acumen. You&#39;ll understand not only how campaigns perform, but why they perform – and how consumer behavior, creative, cultural moments, and emerging platform capabilities can create new opportunities for your clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a senior member of the team, you&#39;ll also help mentor junior strategists, contribute to our team&#39;s evolution, and champion a culture of continuous learning, innovation, and experimentation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own day-to-day paid social strategy across key accounts, including planning, testing, optimizations, forecasting, and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop full funnel media strategies that balance brand building and performance, aligning investment to business objectives and customer behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze campaign performance across platforms and translate insights into clear, actionable recommendations that improve business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with creative teams and clients to shape creative strategy, identifying winning concepts, testing opportunities, and optimization recommendations through performance data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand consumer trends, cultural moments, and platform behaviors to help brands show up in relevant and authentic ways.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal teams and platform partners to bring innovative ideas to clients, including alpha/beta opportunities, new measurement solutions, and emerging platform capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay ahead of platform updates, retail and eCommerce trends, and competitive activity to identify opportunities before they become best practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the creation of clear, compelling storytelling through presentations, POVs, and executive-ready performance summaries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior team members and help elevate strategic thinking and execution across the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
